  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: tried v2.52.4, v2.52. and v2.51.0\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux Ubuntu 22.04.3\r\n\r\nCommit hash: see versions above (downloaded binaries)\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config): `--help`\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer: N/A\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer Command (with flags/config): N/A\r\n\r\nChain/Network: N/A\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n`erigon --help` contents\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nterminal prints `Segmentation fault`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\ndownload the binary into an unpriviledged LXC container (plain vanilla or proxmox)\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n#### Description\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ file erigon\r\n\\erigon: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, BuildID[sha1]=ee68505e9904264f5fedf4444def2bdc924beead, for GNU/Linux 3.2.0, stripped\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have the right binary for my machine\r\n```\r\n$ uname -a\r\nLinux host 5.15.0-84-generic #93-Ubuntu SMP Tue Sep 5 17:16:10 UTC 2023 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut all I get is a `Segmentation fault`. It runs fine on non containerized environment. It also runs fine on WSL2/Ubuntu (which is a type of containerized env, but not LXC). I cannot get it to run inside an unpriviledged LXC container (I won't bother trying to run in a priviledged container bc that is not allowed per company policy).\r\n\r\nIs this something which might be addressed at some point or should I say goodbye to Erigon? I remember being able to run it fine on LXC about a year ago.",
